Here are some important things to know about our covid-19 return to school plan:
- Kids will have temperature checked before they get on a bus or enter a school building. If 100.4 or higher student will stay home and cannot return without a Dr.'s note.
- Students who do not ride a bus to school will not be allowed to enter either building until 7:30MT/8:30CT
- Students need to bring their own water bottles
- Facemasks are not required at this time.

Wauneta-Palisade Parents/Guardians and Patrons: School is scheduled to begin on Wednesday, August 19th. This day will be a 2 hour early dismissal. Regular school days will begin on Thursday, August 20th.

The administration is currently working with the Southwest Public Health Department to develop our plan for returning to school. Currently, we plan to have all students in the building on August 19th. At this point masks will not be required. We are continuously working to develop our full plan to return to learning this fall and hope to have this information out to parents as we get closer to the start of school.
